#!/usr/bin/env python3
# runnerctl — sudoless, config-driven pool manager for self-hosted GitHub Actions runners.
# Single file, Python 3.6+ standard library only.
# https://github.com/flinner/gh-runnerctl
#
# Architecture: ONE supervisor process (`runnerctl daemon`) per machine owns
# every runner process of every pool assigned to that machine as direct
# children, restarting each independently with backoff. The supervisor is
# hosted either as a single user-level systemd service
# (runnerctl-<name>.service) or as a detached process on hosts without a
# systemd user bus. All GitHub work (registration, busy checks, interactive
# token prompts) lives in the CLI commands on the CONTROL machine; daemons
# hold no tokens and are controlled with SIGHUP (rescan) plus per-runner
# marker files.
#
# Multi-machine: a pool may carry `host = "sshalias"`. The control machine
# deploys this script and the config to the host over ssh, runs commands
# there with `--as-host`, and pipes short-lived registration/removal tokens
# over stdin — the GitHub token itself never leaves the control machine.

